author: COMSOL
description: The strength reduction method is a tool for finding the factor of safety (FOS) in geotechnical problems, particularly in slope stability. To determine the factor of safety of a slope, the strength properties of the Mohrâ€“Coulomb model are gradually reduced until failure occurs. A comparison between associative and nonassociative plastic flow is made.
